  {"id"=>294, "name"=>"The Possibility Project", "category"=>"Youth Programs", "website"=>"http://the-possibility-project.org/", "notes"=>"The Possibility Project brings teenagers together to transform the negative forces in their lives and communities into positive action. Through a long-term creative process, our teenagers learn to build relationships across differences, resolve the tough conflicts they face, take on their own responsibility to others and lead.\r\n\r\nParticipants meet 6-7 hours each week for ten months. Together,they explore the complicated issues they encounter daily and take part in workshops and discussions around diversity, leadership, violence prevention, conflict resolution,and social change, as well as training in the performing arts. Stories and perspectives shared in these workshops provide the raw material for an original full-length musical written and performed by the youth themselves. These performances communicate the reality of the participants lives and their vision for change. ", "phone"=>"(212) 924-2300", "address"=>"104 W 27th St, New York, NY 10001", "contact"=>"Kenneth Phillips - artistic director\r\n212-924-9204", "referral"=>"", "eligibility"=>"youth ages 14-21 (flexible)", "insurance"=>"", "created_at"=>DateTime.parse('Wed, 13 May 2015 20:45:03 UTC +00:00'), "updated_at"=>DateTime.parse('Wed, 13 May 2015 20:45:03 UTC +00:00')},
