{"id"=>184, "name"=>"Pride Site I and II", "category"=>"Residential Drug Treatment", "website"=>"http://www.edalliance.org/drug_prevention_treatment_services", "notes"=>"Educational Alliance operates two residential therapeutic communities for adults dealing with chemical dependency.\r\n\r\nPride Site I, is for men only.  Pride Site II, is coed and has specialized services for women.  Clients at both facilities receive treatment tailored specifically to their needs. These services include individual and group psychotherapy, case management, drug counseling, and vocational services.", "phone"=>"646-395-4372 & 646-395-4383", "address"=>"371 East 10th Street New York, NY 10009\r\n25 Avenue D New York, NY 10009", "contact"=>"Norma or Fran in Admissions\r\n\r\nCounselor: David Haynes, 646-299-1385; 212-780-5475 x 4407; Donald_Haynes@edalliance.org", "referral"=>"", "eligibility"=>"", "insurance"=>"", "created_at"=>DateTime.parse('Mon, 23 Feb 2015 19:34:55 UTC +00:00'), "updated_at"=>DateTime.parse('Wed, 11 Mar 2015 19:02:23 UTC +00:00')},
{"id"=>193, "name"=>"CREATE, Inc.", "category"=>"Substance Abuse Mental Health Programs", "website"=>"http://www.createinc.org/services.htm", "notes"=>"Create, Inc. provides a full array of services to persons who are in need. These include: treatment and recovery services for chemical dependent men and women; specialized services for those who have co-occurring mental health and chemical abuse issues; transitional living for homeless young adults; permanent housing and support services for single parent women; vocational counseling, job preparation and placement; day services for the elderly and emergency food distribution for the hungry.  LGBTQ-friendly.\r\n\r\nMEDICALLY SUPERVISED CHEMICAL DEPENDENCY OUTPATIENT TREATMENT PROGRAM - Provides recovery services to men and women, including medical and psychological services, vocational counseling, job placement and basic computer skills, help for specific groups of people including those with specific issues, such as: parole status, mentally ill chemical abusers, anger management, domestic violence and those in need of lifestyle directions. Continental breakfasts and nutritious lunches are served daily.\r\n\r\nPROJECT CREATE RESIDENCE - Provides intensive residential chemical dependence treatment and vocational rehabilitation services to males 18 and above including medical evaluations, counseling, counseling peer support, vocational guidance and placement, 12 step programs, relapse prevention training and life-style direction.\r\n\r\nCREATE YOUNG ADULT RESIDENCES - Home-like transitional living program which is a bridge between the street/shelter/foster care and independent living for men aged 18-25. Residents receive intensive supportive services such as social services counseling, substance abuse counseling, vocational counseling and housing guidance and placement into independent living.\r\n\r\nWESTMINSTER HOUSE - Provides shelter plus care affordable apartment living and supportive services for single mothers and their children. The permanent housing restructures family life after homelessness, addiction or related problems. Counseling, supportive services include; case management, vocational counseling, parenting skills training and extensive use of community resources.\r\n\r\nCREATE FOOD PANTRY - This program was initiated in the 1970's in the spirit of the compassion and generosity of St. Francis of Assisi. We bring food to the tables of our poor and hungry individuals and families in the neighborhood.", "phone"=>"Depends on the program needed - please reference the \"Address\" portion for this information", "address"=>"MEDICALLY SUPERVISED CHEMICAL DEPENDENCY OUTPATIENT TREATMENT PROGRAM\r\n73 Lenox Avenue\r\nNew York City, NY 10026 \r\nMr. Jacques Nir, Clinical Director\r\ntel. (212) 663-1596, fax (212) 666-1323\r\n\r\nPROJECT CREATE RESIDENCE\r\n121-123 West 111th Street\r\nNew York City, NY 10026\r\nMr. Philip Miller, Residential Director \r\ntel: (212) 678-4990, fax (212) 666-6664\r\n\r\nCREATE YOUNG ADULT RESIDENCES \r\n133-135 West 128th Street\r\nNew York City, NY 10026 \r\nMr. Angelo Soto, Residential Director\r\ntel. (212) 662-2000, fax (212) 662-2166\r\n\r\nWESTMINSTER HOUSE\r\n71 Lenox Avenue\r\nNew York City, NY 10026\r\nMs. Felisha Simmons, Case Manager\r\ntel. (212) 663-7260\r\n\r\nCREATE FOOD PANTRY\r\n73 Lenox Avenue, btwn 113th and 114th Streets\r\nNew York City, NY 10026", "contact"=>"Depends on the program needed - please reference the \"Address\" portion for this information", "referral"=>"*** CREATE residences will NOT accept someone with a schizophrenia  diagnosis!", "eligibility"=>"", "insurance"=>"", "created_at"=>DateTime.parse('Fri, 27 Feb 2015 21:50:33 UTC +00:00'), "updated_at"=>DateTime.parse('Mon, 20 Jul 2015 17:37:15 UTC +00:00')},
