{"id"=>158, "name"=>"Center for Employment Opportunities (CEO)", "category"=>"Job Training Programs", "website"=>"http://ceoworks.org/", "notes"=>"Reentry job training program. Pre-employment training, transitional jobs, full-time job placement and retention services. Trade program training and job placement options. Training also available at Bronx Community College (BCC) or at New York City College of Technology and receive a certificate from these institutions.\r\n", "phone"=>"Office: 212.422.4430 ext.368  \r\nCell: 646.423.8413  \r\nFax: 212.785.5898", "address"=>"50 Broadway, NY", "contact"=>"Leâ€™Ann Duran - lduran@ceoworks.org\r\nAgutierrez@ceoworks.org", "referral"=>"Keito Gray kgray@ceoworks.org", "eligibility"=>"", "insurance"=>"", "created_at"=>DateTime.parse('Wed, 07 Jan 2015 19:46:16 UTC +00:00'), "updated_at"=>DateTime.parse('Tue, 17 Mar 2015 19:22:08 UTC +00:00')},
{"id"=>198, "name"=>"Brooklyn Center for Psychotherapy", "category"=>"Mental Health/Behavioral Health Programs", "website"=>"http://www.newdirectionsbrooklyn.com/mental-health/", "notes"=>"The Brooklyn Center for Psychotherapy was established to diagnose and treat the behavioral and personality problems of children, adolescents and adults by carefully evaluating each individual's problems in relation their total environment.  We provide the highest quality of services to those individuals suffering from psychological and behavioral disorders in an accessible, affordable and professional environment aimed at helping them reach their highest potential.  LGBTQ-friendly.\r\n\r\nAll services provided by the Brooklyn Center are available in both English and Spanish.  Our staff consists of psychiatrists, psychologists, registered nurses, social workers and mental health counselors who are dedicated to providing a safe, comfortable and confidential treatment experience.\r\n\r\nOur services include:\r\n- Initial Intake Assessment\r\n- Mental Status Evaluation\r\n- Individual Psychotherapy\r\n- Group Psychotherapy\r\n- Collateral Family Counseling\r\n- Play Therapy\r\n- Psychopharmacotherapy\r\n- Consultation to Agencies & Schools", "phone"=>"Phone: (718) 622-2000\r\nFax:\t(718) 398-3328", "address"=>"300 Flatbush Avenue\r\nBrooklyn, NY 11217", "contact"=>"", "referral"=>"", "eligibility"=>"", "insurance"=>"The Brooklyn Center for Psychotherapy and New Directions provides services at a moderate cost. Most major medical insurance plans as well as Medicaid Managed Care are accepted.\r\n\r\nWe accept:\r\nMedicaid, Medicaid/Medicare, Aetna, Alicare, Americhoice, Amerigroup, Beacon, CenterCare, Empire Blue Cross/Blue Shield, Fidelis, GHI, Healthfirst, HealthPlus, HIP, MetroPlus, Neighborhood Health Provider, New York Presbyterian Community Health Plan, Union Labor Life (Local 813), Value Options, Wellcare, & 1199\r\n\r\nClients are responsible for the following:\r\n- The deductible portion of the insurance\r\n- A co-payment, if necessary, of the difference between the insurance company's payment and the program's fee.\r\n\r\nFees for services are set on a sliding scale.", "created_at"=>DateTime.parse('Mon, 02 Mar 2015 15:10:00 UTC +00:00'), "updated_at"=>DateTime.parse('Mon, 02 Mar 2015 15:10:37 UTC +00:00')},
{"id"=>200, "name"=>"Lutheran Medical Center - Psychiatry and Behavioral Health Services", "category"=>"Mental Health/Behavioral Health Programs", "website"=>"http://www.lutheranhealthcare.org/Main/BehavioralHealth.aspx", "notes"=>"The Lutheran Medical Center Department of Psychiatry and Behavioral Health Sciences offer the Brooklyn community a variety of behavioral health and substance-abuse services.  LGBTQ-friendly.\r\n\r\nInpatient Services Include:\r\n- A 35-bed, Acute Care Psychiatric Unit: Provides psychiatric evaluation and treatment for individuals suffering from psychiatric disorders \r\n- Psychiatric Consultation: Provided by experienced psychiatrists on all medical units of the hospital, available upon request\r\n- Referrals to Longer-term or Residential Care\r\n\r\nEmergency Services Include:\r\n- Psychiatric/Behavioral Health Service Emergency Room: Located within the hospital and near the Medical Emergency Room, it is open to the community 24 hours-a-day, seven days-a-week\r\n- A Psychiatrist and Registered Nurse Always on Duty for Emergency Evaluation and Care\r\n\r\nOutpatient Services Include:\r\n- A Comprehensive Continuum of Mental Health and Substance-abuse Services at Lutheran Family Health Centers Sunset Terrace: Offers individual and group adult and child therapies, couples and family counseling, psychiatric evaluation and medication management\r\n- Healthy Connections Program at Lutheran Family Health Centers Family Support Center: Offers education, counseling and outreach services to anyone in the community experiencing continuing effects of the tragedy\r\n- School based behavioral health in 28 local schools\r\n- Community Medicine Program behavioral health services in shelters", "phone"=>"718-630-6582", "address"=>"150 55th Street\r\nBrooklyn, New York 11220", "contact"=>"", "referral"=>"", "eligibility"=>"", "insurance"=>"We accept Medicaid, Medicare, and most private insurance plans.\r\n\r\n**If you cannot afford to pay, our Financia Assistance Programs may be able to help you. A Patient Service Associate can assist you in applying for these programs:\r\n- Sliding Fee / Charity Care Program\r\n- Medicaid\r\n- Medicare\r\n- Prenatal Care Assistance Program (PCAP)\r\n\r\nInsurances Accepted at Lutheran Include: Aetna, Affinity Health Plan, Americhoice, CarePlus Health Plan, CenterCare, Cigna, Community Care Partners, ElderPlan, Empire Blue Cross Blue Shield, Empire Plan (United Healthcare), Galaxy Health Network, GHI, HealthFirst (excluding their Medicaid product), Health Net, Health Plus Amerigroup, HIP, Horizon Healthcare of New York, Local 1199 National Benefits Fund, MagnaCare, Medicaid, Medicare, MetroPlus, MultiPlan, Neighborhood Health Plan, Oxford Health Plans, Private Healthcare Systems (PHCS), TriCare, United Healthcare, & WellCare", "created_at"=>DateTime.parse('Mon, 02 Mar 2015 15:33:19 UTC +00:00'), "updated_at"=>DateTime.parse('Mon, 02 Mar 2015 15:33:19 UTC +00:00')},
{"id"=>199, "name"=>"New Directions Alcohol and Substance Abuse Treatment Program", "category"=>"Substance Abuse Mental Health Programs", "website"=>"http://www.newdirectionsbrooklyn.com/chemical-dependency/index.php", "notes"=>"New Directions, an out-patient chemical dependency treatment program located in the historic Park Slope section of Brooklyn, has developed an integrated clinical approach to treatment that focuses on the chemically dependent individual and their immediate social environment.  This approach helps individuals to recognize and change their maladaptive behavior, to understand life stressors as they affect chemical dependence, and to develop better coping mechanisms.  It also impacts on the individual's social support system, promoting more constructive reinforcement of sobriety through a focus on the family and social network.  This dual approach serves to encourage and enable the chemically dependent individual to truly seek \"new directions\" in order to develop a more positive lifestyle.  LGBTQ-friendly.\r\n\r\nAll services provided by New Directions are offered in English and Spanish.  Our staff consists of physicians, psychologists, social workers, certified alcohol and substance abuse counselors and creative arts therapists who use a multi-disciplinary approach to meet the needs of each client.\r\n\r\nOur services include:\r\n- Criminal Justice Services: The primary goal of the Criminal Justice Services offered at New Directions is to facilitate the re-integration of clients with criminal justice issues into society by changing negative attitudes and behaviors that could lead to re-engagement in criminal activity.  We strive to have close working relationships with the NYS Department of Parole and Probation, NYC Criminal Courts, Brooklyn Treatment Courts, and the Department of Juvenile Justice.\r\nAs our clients achieve abstinence, they are encouraged to improve social functioning, strengthen family relationships, and seek employment.  Our aim is to help our clients take their place as independent and productive members of society, free from the addictons of chemical dependence and criminal behavior.  Along with weekly individual and group counseling, specialized services include: Supervised Urinalysis & Breathalyzer Screening, Anger Management, Domestic Violence, HIV/AIDS, Parenting Skills & Other Educational Counseling Workshops\r\n- Diagnostic Evaluation\r\n- Psychiatric Evaluation\r\n- Individual Counseling\r\n- Group Counseling\r\n- Spanish Speaking Counseling Service\r\n- Family and Couples Counseling\r\n- Pharmacotherapy\r\n- Dual Diagnosis Care for the Mentally Ill Chemical Abuser\r\n- Weekly Men's/Women's/and Relationship Workshops\r\n- DWI Program\r\n- HIV Testing, Pre- and Post-testing Counseling\r\n- Supervised On-Site Child Care via Patient's Helper Service\r\n- Acupuncture Therapy\r\n- Art Therapy", "phone"=>"Phone: (718) 398-0800\r\nFax:\t(718) 789-8807", "address"=>"500 Atlantic Avenue \r\nBrooklyn, NY 11217", "contact"=>"", "referral"=>"", "eligibility"=>"", "insurance"=>"The Brooklyn Center for Psychotherapy and New Directions provides services at a moderate cost. Most major medical insurance plans as well as Medicaid Managed Care are accepted. \r\n\r\nWe accept: \r\nMedicaid, Medicaid/Medicare, Aetna, Alicare, Americhoice, Amerigroup, Beacon, CenterCare, Empire Blue Cross/Blue Shield, Fidelis, GHI, Healthfirst, HealthPlus, HIP, MetroPlus, Neighborhood Health Provider, New York Presbyterian Community Health Plan, Union Labor Life (Local 813), Value Options, Wellcare, & 1199 \r\n\r\nClients are responsible for the following: \r\n- The deductible portion of the insurance \r\n- A co-payment, if necessary, of the difference between the insurance company's payment and the program's fee. \r\n\r\nFees for services are set on a sliding scale.", "created_at"=>DateTime.parse('Mon, 02 Mar 2015 15:13:22 UTC +00:00'), "updated_at"=>DateTime.parse('Mon, 02 Mar 2015 15:19:22 UTC +00:00')},
{"id"=>202, "name"=>"Mount Sinai Beth Israel - Department of Psychiatry and Behavioral Sciences", "category"=>"Mental Health/Behavioral Health Programs", "website"=>"http://www.wehealny.org/services/psychiatry/index.asp", "notes"=>"Inpatient Services:\r\n- Outpatient Behavioral Sciences\r\n- Supportive/Blended Case Management Program\r\n- (COPAD) Combined Outpatient Psychiatric and Addiction Disorders Program\r\n\r\nClinical Divisions: \r\n- Geriatric Psychiatry\r\n- Consultation-Liaison Psychiatry\r\n- Addiction Psychiatry\r\n- Child Psychiatry\r\n\r\nTreatment Centers & Specialty Programs: \r\n- Center for Anxiety & Post-Traumatic Disorders (Anxiety & Stress Disorders)\r\n- Zirinsky Mood Disorders Center\r\n- Schizophrenia Spectrum Center\r\n- Neurobehavior and Alzheimer's Disease Center\r\n- HIV/AIDS Psychiatry Program\r\n- Primary Care Psychiatry Program\r\n- Brief Psychotherapy Program\r\n- Long Term Psychotherapy Center\r\n- The Family Center for Bipolar Disorder \r\n- Evening/Weekend Programs\r\n\r\nLGBTQ-friendly.", "phone"=>"- Inpatient Services: (212) 420-4650\r\n- Outpatient Behavioral Services: (212) 420-2400 for information or (212) 420-4135 for an evaluation\r\n- Geriatric Psychiatry: (212) 420-2400\r\n- Consultation-Liaison Psychiatry & Psychosomatic Medicine: (212) 420-4230\r\n- Inpatient Addiction Psychiatry/Admissions: (212) 420-4650\r\n- Outpatient Addiction Psychiatry: (212) 420-4135\r\n- Inpatient /Outpatient Stuyvesant Square Rehabilitation Programs: (212)420-2966\r\n- Methadone Maintenance: (212) 726-6800 \r\n- Child and Adolescent Psychiatry: (212) 420-2699\r\n- Zirinsky Mood Disorders Center: (212) 420-2204\r\n- Center for Anxiety & Traumatic Disorders: (212) 420-4135\r\n- Schizophrenia Spectrum Center: (212) 420-4135 \r\n- Neurobehavior and Alzheimerâ€™s Disease Center: (212) 420-4111\r\n- HIV/AIDS Psychiatry Program: (212) 420-4230\r\n- Brief Psychotherapy Program: (212) 420-3819\r\n- Long Term Psychotherapy Center: (212) 844-1543\r\n- Evening/Weekend Programs: (212) 420-2400\r\n- Division of Biological Psychiatry: (212) 844-1598\r\n- Clinical Research Center: (212) 844-2204\r\n- Supportive/Blended Case Management: (212) 420-4250\r\n- Brief Psychotherapy Research Program: (212) 420-3819\r\n- Assertive Community Treatment: (212) 420-2030\r\n- Family Center for Bipolar: (212) 420-2302", "address"=>"Manhattan: \r\nFirst Avenue at 16th Street, New York, NY 10003\r\n10 Union Square East, New York, NY 10003\r\n\r\nBrooklyn: \r\n3201 Kings Highway, Brooklyn, NY 11234", "contact"=>"", "referral"=>"", "eligibility"=>"", "insurance"=>"Access the Hospital Financial Assistance Program webpage for more information:\r\nhttp://www.wehealny.org/services/FinancialAssistance/", "created_at"=>DateTime.parse('Mon, 02 Mar 2015 15:45:16 UTC +00:00'), "updated_at"=>DateTime.parse('Mon, 02 Mar 2015 15:46:52 UTC +00:00')},
{"id"=>201, "name"=>"Project Street Beat", "category"=>"HIV / AIDS Programs", "website"=>"http://www.plannedparenthood.org/planned-parenthood-new-york-city/for-patients/project-street-beat", "notes"=>"Program focused on HIV prevention and access-to-care serving women, men, and teens who live and work on the streets. Provides Rapid HIV/AIDS Testing, Education, and Prevention Interventions, Individual and Group Counseling, Harm Reduction Services, Medical Services, Case Management, Support Groups, and Group-Level Intervention.", "phone"=>"Tel. (212) 965-4850    \r\nFax (212) 965-4844\r\nInfo:(212) 965-4885.", "address"=>"349 East 149th Street\r\nBronx, NY 10451", "contact"=>"", "referral"=>"", "eligibility"=>"", "insurance"=>"", "created_at"=>DateTime.parse('Mon, 02 Mar 2015 15:38:00 UTC +00:00'), "updated_at"=>DateTime.parse('Mon, 02 Mar 2015 15:39:25 UTC +00:00')},
{"id"=>203, "name"=>"Callen-Lorde Community Health Center", "category"=>"HIV / AIDS Programs", "website"=>"http://callen-lorde.org/", "notes"=>"Callen-Lorde provides comprehensive and state-of-the-art HIV/AIDS care and support. Patients have a choice of providers and a range of services that are available under one roof.  LGBTQ-friendly.\r\n\r\nThey include:\r\n- Rapid HIV testing\r\n- HIV Orientation at the first appointment new patients receive one on one education and support to answer any questions about medical treatment and needed services like insurance coverage, government benefits and housing.\r\n- Primary medical care consists of comprehensive, quality medical care with experienced HIV specialist providers.\r\n- Support groups: Please visit our Support Groups page for more information.\r\n- Mental Health: Individual counseling, psychotherapy and annual psychosocial assessments with knowledgeable and sensitive mental health professionals.\r\nMedication adherence counseling provides support and education about HIV infection, prescribed medications, and addressing any side effects.\r\n- Care Coordination offers information, assistance and referrals regarding benefits and entitlements, including insurance, housing, and referrals to other supportive services.\r\n- Sexual Health Counseling helps identify risks for HIV and other sexually transmitted infections and create an individualized risk reduction plan both to promote your health and minimize possible harm regardless of current HIV status.\r\n- Referrals to Clinical Trials: Research programs that seek to improve treatment options for HIV infection.\r\n\r\nFor patients receiving medical care at Callen-Lorde, our Mental Health and Social Services Department offers individual and group counseling to support your emotional and physical well-being. Callen-Lorde is committed to providing services that are affirmative, sex-positive, culturally sensitive, consistent with risk reduction principles, and that promote patient self-determination.\r\n\r\nMental Health and Social Services offered include:\r\n- Mental Health Consultation/Individual Counseling: Patients engaged in medical care at Callen-Lorde who have Medicaid, Medicare, Healthfirst, ADAP, Amidacare, or Metroplus insurance can receive short-term individualized counseling, or, receive a referral to another provider who may better meet your needs.\r\n- Transgender Counseling and Education: The Transgender Counseling and Education session aims to offer specialized information and support to Callen-Lorde patients of transgender experience, including information and support on Hormone Therapy.\r\n- Substance Use Assessment and Referral: If you have concerns about your drug, alcohol, sex and/or internet use, a counselor can connect you to the help you need. The service is flexible. Whether you are looking to reduce your use or completely stop, our counselor can offer you a range of referrals.\r\n- Psychiatric Services: Our staff psychiatrists are primarily available for an initial evaluation visit and follow-up visits based on your needs. A referral to our psychiatrist is usually made by your medical or mental health provider if they and you think medication may help your mental health problems.\r\n- Support Groups: We offer a range of groups providing support and counseling in a variety of areas. Our support groups are open to anyone who is a medical patient at Callen-Lorde, regardless of their insurance coverage.\r\n", "phone"=>"Phone: (212) 271-7200\r\nFax: (212) 271-7225", "address"=>"Callen-Lorde Community Health Center: \r\nMain Site â€“ 356 West 18th St, New York, NY 10011 \r\n\r\nCallen-Lorde Seventeen: \r\nThe Thea Spyer Center for Integrated Health â€“ 230 West 17th St, New York, NY 10011 ", "contact"=>"", "referral"=>"", "eligibility"=>"", "insurance"=>"Access their Health Insurance Outreach & Enrollment webpage:\r\nhttp://callen-lorde.org/getinsured/", "created_at"=>DateTime.parse('Mon, 02 Mar 2015 15:56:53 UTC +00:00'), "updated_at"=>DateTime.parse('Mon, 02 Mar 2015 15:56:53 UTC +00:00')},
