{"id"=>204, "name"=>"Community Healthcare Network", "category"=>"HIV / AIDS Programs", "website"=>"http://www.chnnyc.org/services/transgender-lgbt", "notes"=>"Transgender & LGBTQ Program: Offers primary (basic) health care, preventive health services, weekly workshops with presentations by staff and invited guests, support group meetings, counseling by licensed mental health therapist, & HIV counseling and testing\r\n\r\nBehavioral Health Program:\r\n- Social Work Services: Offers private and supportive counseling for family and relationship issues, HIV/AIDS, depression, sexual abuse, domestic violence, & drug abuse\r\n- Outpatient Mental Health Treatment Program: Offers psychiatric evaluations, help managing medicines, one-on-one therapy, & family therapy\r\n\r\nOur therapists speak many languages, including English, Spanish, French, and Haitian Creole. We offer appointments during the day, evening, and on some Saturdays.", "phone"=>"CHN Main Number: (866) 246-8259", "address"=>"Transgender & LGBTQ Program:\r\n- Bronx Health Center: 975 Westchester Avenue, Bronx, NY 10459\r\n- Catherine M. Abate Health Center: 150 Essex Street, New York NY 10002\r\n- Family Health Center: 90-04 161st Street, Jamaica NY 11432\r\n\r\nBehavioral Health Program:\r\n- Catherine M. Abate Health Center: 150 Essex Street, New York NY 10002\r\n- Bronx Health Center: 975 Westchester Avenue, Bronx, NY 10459\r\n- Tremont Health Center: 4215 Third Avenue 2nd FL, Bronx NY 10457\r\n- CABS Health Center: 94-98 Manhattan Avenue, Brooklyn, NY 11206\r\n- Dr. Betty Shabazz Health Center: 999 Blake Avenue, Brooklyn, NY 11208\r\n- Caribbean House Health Center: 1167 Nostrand Avenue, Brooklyn, NY 11225", "contact"=>"", "referral"=>"", "eligibility"=>"", "insurance"=>"Access their Cost of Care webpage for more information:\r\nhttp://www.chnnyc.org/cost-of-care\r\n\r\nS.H.I.N.E. Project \r\nIf you do not have health insurance and identify as transgender, lesbian, gay, bisexual, and/or queer, our S.H.I.N.E. Project can help you get the health care that you need. Please note: You do not have to be a U.S. citizen to use S.H.I.N.E. services.  Access their S.H.I.N.E. Project webpage for more information:\r\nhttp://www.chnnyc.org/services/special-programs/shine-program", "created_at"=>DateTime.parse('Mon, 02 Mar 2015 16:15:58 UTC +00:00'), "updated_at"=>DateTime.parse('Mon, 02 Mar 2015 16:15:58 UTC +00:00')},
