{"id"=>72, "name"=>"Arms Acres", "category"=>"Substance Abuse Mental Health Programs", "website"=>"http://www.armsacres.com/behavioral-health-programs", "notes"=>"Arms Acres provides inpatient and outpatient services to those suffering from alcohol and/or substance abuse issues.  The multidisciplinary treatment team at Arms Acres includes physicians, psychiatrists, nurses, certified alcoholism and substance abuse counselors, social workers, family specialists and activities specialists. \r\n\r\nDetox Program:\r\nThe detoxification program at Arms Acres is designed for patients experiencing withdrawal symptoms, including physical or psychiatric complications, associated with chemical dependence. Services include; medical evaluation, psychiatric assessment, individual and group counseling and educational groups/lectures. Arms Acres also provides suboxone induction, maintenance and monitoring when clinically indicated. At the conclusion of detox, personalized aftercare planning equips patients with the tools necessary to maintain and extend progress. Patients may be transferred to Arms Acres rehab or may be discharged for transitional care on an outpatient basis.\r\n\r\nRehab (Adult Program): \r\nIncludes a variety of services such as Evaluation/Assessment/Diagnosis, Individual Treatment Planning, Workforce programming, Dual Focus Group, Nutrition Education/Dietary Needs Addressed, Family Programming, Relapse Prevention, Stress Management & Anger Reduction, Therapeutic Recreation â€“ Including yoga and swimming, Art Therapy, GLBT, Readiness for Discharge Group, Equine Therapy, Cultural Awareness Education, Enhancement of Twelve-Step Affiliations, & Strong and Individualized Aftercare referrals\r\n\r\nRehab (Adolescent Program):\r\nTo ensure continued health and success post-treatment, Arms Acres utilizes two evidenced based treatment approaches to engage adolescents in the treatment process despite cognitive, developmental and motivation deficits. We utilize both Motivational Enhancement and Cognitive Behavioral therapeutic approaches in engaging, educating and treating adolescents.\r\n\r\nFamily Program:\r\nArms Acres recognizes that chemical dependency is a disease that not only impacts the addict physically, mentally, and spiritually but also family members and other loved ones as well as the family structure.  During the Family Program participants explore the impact of the disease, difficulties of the early recovery process and learn ways to improve communication patterns among other topics.\r\n\r\nFitness/ Recreation Program:\r\nThrough the use of fitness, outdoor and expressive activities, patients are given an opportunity to learn new activities and coping skills and more importantly they can use these activities to maintain a sober and healthy lifestyle in the future.\r\n\r\nOutpatient Services:\r\ndesigned to provide a broad range of treatment to clients in need of alcohol and substance abuse counseling. Services are flexible in orientation and content and assist clients in need of chemical dependency treatment.", "phone"=>"914.576.6853     \r\nFor detox, call: 1-888-227-4641  ", "address"=>"75 Seminary Hill Rd, Carmel NY 10512", "contact"=>"Angel Bosques Jr., MA, LMSW Cell: 646-645-0073", "referral"=>"Arms Acres Intake: 888-227-4641. Call or refer online.", "eligibility"=>"", "insurance"=>"Arms Acres is in network with most commercial insurance companies, managed-care programs, and Medicaid.  Once an intake is completed, we will contact your insurance company to explore your coverage AND the procedure to follow for admission.  Most of the time, an insurance company will require clinical information to determine whether or not you meet the criteria for this level of care.  We at Arms Acres provide â€œpre-certification assessmentsâ€ and work with your insurance company to get approval for your admission to Arms Acres.\r\n\r\nPatients who are interested in extending their stay after insurance coverage is exhausted OR those individuals without  any coverage at all, may consider our self-pay plan.", "created_at"=>DateTime.parse('Sun, 16 Nov 2014 18:27:12 UTC +00:00'), "updated_at"=>DateTime.parse('Fri, 06 Mar 2015 19:57:14 UTC +00:00')},
