{"id"=>218, "name"=>"Family Justice Center", "category"=>"Domestic Violence Related Programs", "website"=>"http://www.nyc.gov/html/ocdv/html/faq/fjc.shtml", "notes"=>"A Mayorâ€™s Office program to Combat Domestic Violence. These FJCs provide criminal justice, civil legal and social services in one location. When visiting a Center, victims can meet with a prosecutor, speak with a trained counselor, and apply for housing and financial assistance in just one place. Each FJC has a Childrenâ€™s Room where children ages 3 and up can play in a safe and supervised space while their parents receive services. Six City agencies.", "phone"=>" (718) 508-1220", "address"=>"198 East 161 Street, Bronx, NY 10451", "contact"=>"", "referral"=>"Just walk in to the FJC Monday through Friday 9:00 am to 5:00 pm. In addition, some special programs and appointments are held after 5:00 pm. However, as the FJCs are busy walk-in Centers, if it is your first visit, it is advisable to come in the morning if possible.", "eligibility"=>" Any victim of domestic violence can utilize services at the FJCs, regardless of whether there is a pending criminal or civil case against the abuser and regardless of whether the victim has separated from their abusive partner.", "insurance"=>"", "created_at"=>DateTime.parse('Mon, 09 Mar 2015 16:43:06 UTC +00:00'), "updated_at"=>DateTime.parse('Mon, 09 Mar 2015 16:43:06 UTC +00:00')},
{"id"=>230, "name"=>"Taylor Mayd: Services and Treatment for the Community", "category"=>"Substance Abuse Mental Health Programs", "website"=>"http://www.taylormaydinc.com/services.html", "notes"=>"Outpatient Services: \r\nIncludes individual, family, and group counseling, as well as aftercare services; including:\r\n- Alcohol & Substance Abuse Classes\r\n- Parenting Classes (Spanish & English)\r\n- Anger Management Classes (Spanish & English)\r\n- Domestic Violence Classes\r\n- DUI/ DWI Classes (Spanish & English)\r\n- Stress Management Classes\r\n- Family Counseling\r\n- Eating Disorders, Addiction & Recovery\r\n- Groups\r\n- Addiction & Recovery: For nicotine cessation, gambling, & cutting\r\n- Veterans & Military Families\r\n- Prescription & OTC Drug Abuse\r\n\r\n*Spanish-speaking services are available*\r\n\r\n**AND they DO drug test your client!**", "phone"=>"718-829-3617", "address"=>"51 Westchester Square \r\nBronx, New York 10461", "contact"=>"", "referral"=>"You can access their referral form here: http://www.taylormaydinc.com/referral-form.html ", "eligibility"=>"", "insurance"=>"Visit their \"Self-Pay Schedule\" webpage for more info: http://www.taylormaydinc.com/self-pay-program.html \r\n\r\nIt is unclear as to whether or not they accept insurance.", "created_at"=>DateTime.parse('Thu, 12 Mar 2015 14:25:10 UTC +00:00'), "updated_at"=>DateTime.parse('Thu, 12 Mar 2015 15:18:15 UTC +00:00')},
