{"id"=>233, "name"=>"Claremont Neighborhood Centers", "category"=>"Youth Programs", "website"=>"http://www.claremontcenter.org/default.html", "notes"=>"Programs Offered:\r\n- Project AIM: An evidence based project with elements of group-level youth development intervention that assist in the prevention/risk reduction behaviors of HIV among middle school youth. A CAPP-PREP program.\r\n- Raising Our Daughters: For current teen moms or pregnant teen moms between the ages of 10-20. The program emphasizes the role of maternal protectiveness, motivates adolescents to make healthy sexual decisions and decrease risky sexual behaviors, encourages young girls to take on sexual responsibility and accountability, increases their awareness of the effects of HIV/AIDS on inner city communities, and helps moms in all respects in\r\n becoming proud moms. We also have mentors who serve as guest speakers and are dedicated in helping young girls make a difference in their lives. A CAPP-PREP program.", "phone"=>"", "address"=>"489 East 169th Street\r\nBronx, NY 10456", "contact"=>"", "referral"=>"", "eligibility"=>"", "insurance"=>"", "created_at"=>DateTime.parse('Thu, 12 Mar 2015 20:55:02 UTC +00:00'), "updated_at"=>DateTime.parse('Thu, 12 Mar 2015 20:55:02 UTC +00:00')},
{"id"=>67, "name"=>"St Lukes Roosevelt ", "category"=>"Substance Abuse Mental Health Programs", "website"=>"http://www.whpnyc.org/", "notes"=>"Variety of programs for clients seeking help with addictions. There is an outpatient drug and alcohol treatment program. The Women's Health Project Treatment is a program for clients who are survivors of abuse or trauma, many of whom also struggle with addiction, individual and group psychotherapy, and pharmacotherapy. The Access Center is a psychiatric clinic that provides initial evaluative entry and psychiatric screening.", "phone"=>"212-523-3061 (Women's Health Project Treatment)\r\n212-523-8080 (Access Center Psychiatric Clinic)\r\n212-523-4093 (For Professional Referrals)\r\n", "address"=>"411 W 114th St. suite 6C", "contact"=>"", "referral"=>"Andrea Johnson 212-523-7693", "eligibility"=>"", "insurance"=>"", "created_at"=>DateTime.parse('Sun, 16 Nov 2014 18:27:12 UTC +00:00'), "updated_at"=>DateTime.parse('Fri, 27 Mar 2015 19:20:21 UTC +00:00')},
{"id"=>223, "name"=>"Metropolitan Center for Mental Health", "category"=>"Mental Health/Behavioral Health Programs", "website"=>"http://www.metropolitancenter.com/services/", "notes"=>"Metropolitan's staff consists of highly trained, committed psychiatrists, psychologists, social workers and other mental health professionals attuned to the needs of the community.\r\n\r\nServices provided include:\r\n- Individual psychotherapy\r\n- Play therapy\r\n- Parent counseling\r\n- Couples communication\r\n- Family counseling\r\n- Group psychotherapy\r\n- Psychological testing\r\n- Medication therapy: Psychopharmacological services are provided by staff psychiatrists as a part of ongoing therapy and as an aid in crisis situations\r\n\r\nSpecialty services include:\r\n- Hispanic family service\r\n- Child & adolescent program\r\n- FAIR (Families and Individuals in Recovery)", "phone"=>"See \"address\" section for phone numbers specific to location", "address"=>"160 West 86th Street\r\nNew York, NY 10024\r\nPhone: (212) 362.8755\r\nFax: (212) 362.0168\r\n\r\n1090 St. Nicholas Avenue\r\nNew York, New York 10032\r\nPhone: (212) 543-0777\r\nFax: (212) 543-2378\r\n\r\n336 Central Park West\r\nNew York, NY 10025\r\nPhone: (212) 864.3666\r\nFax: (212) 864.7117", "contact"=>"", "referral"=>"Intake appointments are offered at 160 West 86th Street and 1090 St. Nicholas Avenue locations and are scheduled by telephone. To schedule an initial appointment, call the location of choice to speak with the Reception desk. Please have your insurance information ready.", "eligibility"=>"", "insurance"=>"The Clinic accepts Medicaid, Medicare and several Managed Care Plans (Commercial plans, Medicaid plans and Medicare Advantage).\r\n\r\nThe Clinic offers an out-of-pocket fee, based on a sliding scale, for uninsured persons. There is a flat fee of $35 for the initial Intake evaluation and a $45 flat fee for a psychiatric evaluation (if one is needed). Individual fees thereafter are set on a sliding scale, based on proof of income (i.e. W2 , Pay stub).", "created_at"=>DateTime.parse('Wed, 11 Mar 2015 15:29:00 UTC +00:00'), "updated_at"=>DateTime.parse('Wed, 11 Mar 2015 15:29:00 UTC +00:00')},
