{"id"=>114, "name"=>"St. Barnabas Hospital", "category"=>"Substance Abuse Mental Health Programs", "website"=>"www.stbarnabashospital.org", "notes"=>"1) Inpatient Psychiatric Services:\r\nOffers a 49-bed unit serving adults aged 18 and older with psychiatric disorders. Experienced professionals from multiple disciplines, including Psychiatry, Psychology, Nursing, Social Work and Activity/Recreational Therapy, staff the units.\r\n\r\n2) Outpatient Psychiatric Services: located at Fordham-Tremont Community Mental Health Center\r\n\r\n2) Detox:\r\nThis is an inpatient detox program for alcohol and opiates.  They provide special care for pregnant women. Individual and group counseling in English & Spanish.  They have 24-hour 7-day-a-week admission and offer continuity of care with follow-up treatment on site.  For services after 2PM or a holiday and weekends, client must go through ER.\r\n\r\n3) Outpatient Substance Abuse Program:\r\nThis is an Outpatient Alcohol and Substance Abuse Program for adults (18+). They offer individual and group therapy as well as supportive services to family members. They provide DWI services.  Provides referrals to vocational services.  Provides transportation.  Offers parenting skills classes.  Accepts walk-ins. Groups and individual counseling offered in Spanish.", "phone"=>"See \"Address\" section for this info", "address"=>"Inpatient Psychiatric Services\r\n4422 Third Avenue\r\nBronx, NY 10457\r\n718-960-6159 \r\n\r\nOutpatient Psychiatric Services - Fordham-Tremont Community Mental Health Center\r\n2021 Grand Concourse, 6th floor\r\nBronx, NY 10453\r\nIntake: 718-960-3071\r\n\r\nDetox\r\n4535 3rd Avenue\r\nBronx, NY 10457\r\n718-960-6636\r\n\r\nOutpatient Substance Abuse \r\n4451 3rd Avenue, 2nd Floor\r\nBronx, NY 10457\r\n718-960-6588", "contact"=>"", "referral"=>"Call or walk in.", "eligibility"=>"Anyone age 18+ who is in need of outpatient substance abuse treatment.", "insurance"=>"Medicaid & sliding scale", "created_at"=>DateTime.