{"id"=>300, "name"=>"LIFT - New York", "category"=>"Community Center Providing Services", "website"=>"", "notes"=>"Works to lift people out of poverty for good by supporting community members in acheiving their personal, social, and financial goals. LIFT - New York serves community members with children under the age of eight in navigating resources in the following areas: 1) child care and education 2) housing 3) employment 4) public benefits 5) legal civil clinic 6) financial and tax preparation.\r\n\r\nOpen for member services Monday, Tuesday, Thursday, and Friday's from 9am-4pm. Walk-in's welcome, but encouraged to schedule appointment beforehand. Call 347-584-4010 for appointment. ", "phone"=>"347-584-4010", "address"=>"349 East 149th Street, Suite 500 | Bronx, NY 10451\r\n", "contact"=>"Sandy Guillaume - Public Benefits Coordinator\r\nTel: 347-584-4010  Fax. 718.220.5418\r\nsguillaume@liftcommunities.org\r\n\r\nUnique Brathwaite - Program Director\r\nubrathwaite@liftcommunities.org", "referral"=>" Front Desk Associate at (347) 584-4010.  Call to make appointment ", "eligibility"=>"must be a parent of a child 8 years old or younger", "insurance"=>"free", "created_at"=>DateTime.parse('Mon, 15 Jun 2015 20:06:14 UTC +00:00'), "updated_at"=>DateTime.parse('Mon, 15 Jun 2015 20:06:14 UTC +00:00')},
{"id"=>301, "name"=>"Court Involved Youth Initiative", "category"=>"Youth Programs", "website"=>"", "notes"=>"Kerry Green can provide weekly individual counseling sessions to young people free of charge. She's been a great advocate for my clients, and will focus on whatever kid needs (impulse control, anger management, bereavement, etc.). Also very quick with responses, which is a rarity.. \r\n\r\nThey also do mental health screenings, clinical assessments, and expedited referrals for drug treatment, education, and vocational services. In short, THE BEST.\r\n", "phone"=>"917-239-3096\r\n", "address"=>"910 E 172nd St. 4th Floor Bronx, NY", "contact"=>"Kerry Green, LMSW\r\nkgreen@childrensaidsociety.org", "referral"=>"There's a PDF in the shared documents folder ", "eligibility"=>"Youth ages 14-21 with criminal justice contact (don't need an open criminal case, and no charges too severe as of now)", "insurance"=>"Do not need insurance. Individual counseling sessions are FREE. For outside referrals, insurance may be necessary ", "created_at"=>DateTime.parse('Tue, 16 Jun 2015 19:08:58 UTC +00:00'), "updated_at"=>DateTime.parse('Wed, 17 Jun 2015 13:02:46 UTC +00:00')},
